<div class = 'main-area'>
	<h2>Past Projects</h2>
	<div id = 'past-projects-container' >
		<div class = 'past-project-div'>
			<h3>PBL Links</h3>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>What:</b> A custom url shortener and internal search engine for PBL</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>How:</b> We indexed all of PBL's over 10,000 resources from Box, Google Drive, Youtube, Flickr, and more into our database and exposed their scraped fulltext to Elasticsearch. We built a chrome extension to make accessing, discovering, and creating links a seamless experience. For reliablity and scalability we've deployed multiple containers of our webserver.</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Technologies:</b> Docker, Elasticsearch, Haproxy, Memcached, Postgres, Ruby on Rails, Parse</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class = 'past-project-div'>
			<h3>PBL Members Portal</h3>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>What:</b> A Members Portal for tracking every PBL Member's information, schedules, points, attendance, and more</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>How:</b> We build a traditional Ruby on Rails website</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Technologies:</b> Docker, Ruby on Rails, Parse</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>More:</b> <a href = 'http://pbl.link/portal-git'>pbl.link/portal-git</a></li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class = 'past-project-div'>
			<h3>Deliberations Engine</h3>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>What:</b> A generic deliberations engine that creates recommendations on which committees are best for which members based on applicant preferences and committee chair preferences.</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>How:</b> We used a modified version of the Gale-Shapley (stable marriage) algorithm</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Technologies:</b> CS70, Ruby on Rails</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>More:</b> <a href = 'http://pbl.link/deliberations-algorithm'>pbl.link/deliberations-algorithm</a></li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class = 'past-project-div'>
			<h3>WD Elevator Challenge</h3>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>What:</b> A fun elevator challenge for PBL's Apprentice Challenge program</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>How:</b> We found an integer programming problem (scheduling elevators to pick up passengers) and created a challenge website to encourage PBL members to think of creative algorithms.</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Technologies:</b> Flask, Parse</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>More:</b> <a href = 'http://pbl.link/elevator-scheduling'>pbl.link/elevator-scheduling</a></li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class = 'past-project-div'>
			<h3>Facebook Matchmaker</h3>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>What:</b> A fun matchmaking widget that generates suggestions for potential romantic matches based on social gestures and interactions on Faceboook</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>How:</b> We scraped PBL's Facebook pages and groups and created ranking lists based on likes and comments. Feeding those into the stable marriage algorithm, we generated suggested matches for PBL Members.</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Technologies:</b> Facebook SDK, Flask</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
