<div class = 'main-area'>
	<h1 style>Apply</h1>
	<h3>Show us what you can do!</h3>
	<p>We want teammates who dream big and are ready to make a difference!</p>
	<p>Please complete one challenge and submit your solution to berkeleypbl.webdev@gmail.com</p> 
	<p>Dont stress about any of these! The idea is for you to have fun and show us what you're about!</p>
	<p>You may use any tool at your disposal. We google about 99% of what we do :)</p>
	<p>Email us any questions you have at berkeleypbl.webdev@gmail.com!</p>

	<h3>Challenges</h3>
	<div class = 'challenge-container row'>
		<div class = 'challenge-div'>
			<h4>Coding Challenge: Alien Dictionary</h4>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Description:</b> In the english alphabet, A&lt;B&lt;C&lt;D etc... You uncovered an alien dictionary and want to find out their "alphabet". The words in the dictionary are sorted in alphabetical order, but you dont know the order of their characters. (In this problem, for example, O&lt;I&lt;U...)</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Submitting:</b> Using the dictionary entries (below), return the characters in alphabetical order. For example, the characters in alphabetical order for English are (ABCDEFGHIJKL....). Send us the sorted characters and any code/work you used to generate the sorting.</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Dictionary:</b> <a href = 'http://pbl.link/alien-dictionary'>pbl.link/alien-dictionary</a>
				</li>
			</ul>

		</div>

		<div class = 'challenge-div'>
			<h4>UI Challenge: Cat Gallery</h4>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Description:</b> You have a brilliant plan for a hot new website: a cat picture gallery! Use the images we provide below and display them in your gallery.</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Constraints:</b> 
					<ul>
						<li>Images can be sized down but not up</li>
						<li>Images must retain their original aspect ratio (ie: a square image cannot be resized into a rectangle)</li>
						<li>Images must fit in a rectangular area with minimal unused space inside</li>
						<li>Images may not overlap</li>
						<li>All cat images must be present in the gallery</li>
						<li>The width of the gallery must be 600px. Do not exceed this width, and try not to go under the width either</li>
					</ul>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Resources:</b> <a href = 'http://pbl.link/cat-images'>pbl.link/cat-images</a></li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Submitting:</b> Show us the finalized gallery (a .html page); how did you decide how to rearrange the images?</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class = 'challenge-div'>
			<h4>Engineering Challenge: DIY</h4>
			<ul class = 'list-group'>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Description:</b> Show us something you built!</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Details:</b> This doesn't have to be software related. It can be any hack (hardware or software)!</li>
				<li class = 'list-group-item'><b>Submitting:</b> Briefly describe the project in your email to us. What did it solve? How did you built it? What were the challenges? We will followup with an informal chat about your project.</li>

			</ul>
		</div>

	</div>

